Date:  21/10/1933
Source:  Press, The
Author:
Vol / Page:  15
Edition:
Quote:  Fleece: (1) The whole of a sheep's wool. (Canterbury Rhymes) (2) The main part of a sheep's wool, which is picked up in one, skirted  and rolled. This is sold as fleece wool, as opposed to locks,  bellies and pieces. (C.)
Notes:  Acland Glossary

